<item>
            <title>[SPARK-40829] STORED AS serde in CREATE TABLE LIKE view does not work</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-40829</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-29839&quot; title=&quot;Supporting STORED AS in CREATE TABLE LIKE&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPARK-29839&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPARK-29839&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; added the feat for supporting STORED AS in CREATE TABLE LIKE, and we could use this syntax to create a table with specified serde based on a existing &lt;b&gt;table or view.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I found that if we create a table based on a &lt;b&gt;view&lt;/b&gt;, the serde of created table is always parquet.&#160; However, if we use &lt;b&gt;USING syntax&lt;/b&gt;&#160; (&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-29421&quot; title=&quot;Using &amp;#39;USING provider&amp;#39; to specify a different table provider in CREATE TABLE LIKE&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPARK-29421&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPARK-29421&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;) to create a table with specified serde based a &lt;b&gt;view&lt;/b&gt;, we can get the correct serde.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think we shoud fix this to add specified serde for the created table when using &lt;b&gt;create table like view&lt;/b&gt; &lt;b&gt;stored as&lt;/b&gt; syntax.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
